







































Jane L. Mendillo | GM Board of Directors





























Leadership













Back to Board of Directors




Jane L. Mendillo
Retired President & Chief Executive Officer,  Harvard Management CompanyDirector Since: 2016







Ms. Mendillo served as President and Chief Executive Officer of the Harvard Management Company (“HMC”) from 2008 to 2014, where she managed Harvard University’s approximately $37 billion global endowment and related assets. From 2002 to 2008, she served as the Chief Investment Officer of Wellesley College. Prior to that, Ms. Mendillo spent 15 years at HMC in various investment roles. She serves as chair of the investment committee of the Partners Healthcare System, is a member of the board of directors and investment committees of the Mellon Foundation, senior investment advisor to the Old Mountain Private Trust Company, and a member of the board of Berklee College of Music.
Ms. Mendillo is also a director at Lazard Ltd.

























































































