Insider Activity


Individual




Jane L. Mendillo



Ms. Jane L. Mendillo, CFA MBA, is President & Chief Executive Officer at Harvard Management Co., Inc. and President & Director at Blue Marble Holdings Corp.
Ms. Mendillo re-joined Harvard Management in July 2008. She returned to HMC after serving as Chief Investment Officer of Wellesley College from 2002 to 2008. Prior to Wellesley, she spent 15 years at HMC where her responsibilities included oversight of all of the portfolio's outside managed assets as Vice President of External Management, after serving as a member of the Internal Equity and Private Equity management teams. She began her business career as a management consultant with Bain & Company in Boston. She a member of the Boston Security Analysts Society, Inc., the Council on Foreign Relations, the Boston Committee on Foreign Relations, and the Boston Economic Club. She serves as a member of the Board of Directors for the Boston Foundation, as well as on the Investment Committee at both Partners Healthcare and the Rockefeller Foundation.
Ms. Mendillo earned a BA and an MBA from Yale University. She is also a CFA charter holder.



